<promed@promedmail.org>
[It would be interesting to know the strain of rabies involved. If this
were occurring in South America, we might believe it to be a bat rabies
strain, generally coming from bats.
Vaccination of the pets is a wise move.
Rabies in cattle is remarkable, and, once seen, is not easy to forget. The
animals bellow with a sound that might more aptly be described as something
from a horror movie. It is no wonder the townspeople are quite scared.
The article is unclear whether these people are receiving post-exposure
prophylaxis (PEP), or, if they are receiving preventative treatment. If it
is PEP, then the number of injections seems very high. If it is a
preventative vaccine, it would be nice to know the origin, and, whether it
is duck embryo, human diploid, or rhesus strain. - Mod.TG]
